description:
For some reason, the os-floating-ips method never lists any associated vms. For example;

curl -i http://192.168.1.111:8774/v2/3ae8d3adc19f483caa781d3cccaa8812/os-floating-ips -X GET -H "X-Auth-Project-Id: demo" -H "User-Agent: python-novaclient" -H "Accept: application/json" -H "X-Auth-Token: d200f5c5d7314d0ab9347e93787c13ef"

returns

{"floating_ips": [{"ip": "172.24.4.225", "fixed_ip": "10.0.0.2", "id": 1, "pool": "nova"}]}

ideally, it would return

{"floating_ips": [{"ip": "172.24.4.225", "fixed_ip": "10.0.0.2", "vm_instance_id": "4a7075e9-05f7-45ea-9bc0-22419ba16afe", "vm_reservation_id": "r-btyhwy1j", "id": 1, "pool": "nova"}

